  <bioghist id="aspace_62f96a79e049624cb99b64bdb708ab1f">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>From its founding until 1969, the department was known as Household Economics and Management; from 1969 to 1977, it was called Consumer Economics and Public Policy; since 1977, it has been the Dept. of Consumer Economics and Housing.</p><p> The New York State College of Home Economics is now the New York State College of Human Ecology.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_e46200449d2187fe2761c37b33e72928">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Includes department correspondence, 1928-1960, primarily letters of Helen Canon; also correspondence of Jean Warren, Edna Van Horn, Dorothy Dickens, Hazel Kyrk, Day Monroe, the Family Economics Division and Family Economics-Home Management Division of the American Home Economics Association. Issues of <title>School of Living</title> Bulletins, 1938-1942; and photographs and other material concerning Mabel Rollins, Lucille Williamson and Jean Warren. Also, thirty-five home account study records from a New York State study conducted by Sally Manning, 1957-1958; 4 volume mss. history "Development of the Department of Economics of the Household and Household Management as Recorded in Documents," 1900-1953; 2 volumes "Schedule Forms," 1929-1960; and 2 volumes of abstracts of Ph.D. theses, Dept. of Household Economics and Management, 1938-1966.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <relatedmaterial id="aspace_460429a5065ce1b016a5c10626ac8b40">
    <head>RELATED MATERIALS</head>
<p>The film <extref href="https://media.library.cornell.edu/media/Within+Your+ReachA+Storage+of+Glass+and+China/1_sfgpw6by/7781881"> <title>Within Your Reach</title> </extref> from this collection has been digitized and can be found on Cornell's Library Media Space website along with other Home Economics and related films.</p>  </relatedmaterial>
